{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, strict rules for citation and referencing, as outlined by the American Psychological Association (APA, 2020), underscore the need for dedicated investigation.",
    "AI has made significant progress towards generating text that closely resembles human-written content, raising questions about its accuracy and integrity in scientific writing (Alkaissi & McFarlane, 2023).",
    "While AI models like GPT-4 are becoming increasingly sophisticated, their performance in scientific writing, especially in the field of school psychology, remains uncertain.",
    "Surprisingly, there is currently no research available that specifically examines the use of any version of ChatGPT for writing psychological papers, despite the fact that writing is a crucial role of psychology professors (Alkaissi & McFarlane, 2023).",
    "Additionally, the American Psychological Association (APA) has stringent rules for citation and referencing in scientific writing (APA, 2020)."
  ]
}